vald>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/797.html |title=Augvald |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=29 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Castlehill||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk in the [[Bristol Channel]] off [[Minehead]], [[Somerset]] by [[Heinkel He 111]] aircraft of [[Kampfgeschwader 27]], [[Luftwaffe]] with the loss of all but one crew.<ref name=NH034112/><ref name=seekrieg194103/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Madge Wildfire||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=The cargo ship ran aground at Congress Point, [[Derbyhaven]], [[Isle of Man]] and was wrecked.<ref name=MW>{{cite web |url=http://www.clydesite.co.uk/clydebuilt/viewship.asp?id=20191 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160202193508/http://www.clydesite.co.uk/clydebuilt/viewship.asp?id=20191 |url-status=usurped |archive-date=2 February 2016 |title=Launched 1905: SS Jerfalcon |publisher=Clydesite |accessdate=22 December 2011}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Pacific|1915|2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Convoy HX 109]]: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean {{convert|180|nmi|km}} west south west of the [[Faroe Islands]] by {{GS|U-95|1940|2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of 33 of her 34 crew. The survivor was rescued by the trawler ''Dora'' ([[File:Light Blue Flag of Iceland.svg|22px]] [[Kingdom of Iceland|Iceland]]).<ref name=NH034112/><ref name=Pacific>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/798.html |title=Pacific |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=20 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Simaloer||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Netherlands}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean ({{coord|56|40|N|10|46|W}}) by [[Focke-Wulf Fw 200]] aircraft of I ''Staffeln'', [[Kampfgeschwader 40]], Luftwaffe with the loss of two crew. Thirty-nine s