go ship was torpedoed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean ({{coord|20|51|N|20|32|W}}) by {{GS|U-124|1940|2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of 28 of her 40 crew. Survivors were rescued by {{HMS|Faulknor|H62|6}} ({{navy|UK}}) and {{SS|Guido||2}} ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}).<ref name=NH034112/><ref name=Hindpool>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/807.html |title=Hindpool |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=25 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Lahore||2}} \n|flag={{Flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Convoy SL 67]]: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean ({{coord|21|03|N|20|38|W}}) by {{GS|U-124|1940|2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}). All 82 crew were rescued by {{HMS|Forester|H74|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=NH034112/><ref name=StanL>{{cite web |url=http://www.mariners-l.co.uk/WWIStandardShipsL-W.htm#L-M-N |title=WWI Standard Built Ships L - W |publisher=Mariners |accessdate=8 May 2011}}</ref><ref name=Lahore>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/810.html |title=Lahore |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=25 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Nardana||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Convoy SL 67]]: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean ({{coord|20|51|N|20|32|W}}) by {{GS|U-120|1940|2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of 19 of her 107 crew. Survivors were rescued by {{HMS|Faulknor|H62|6}} and {{HMS|Forester|H74|6}} (both {{navy|UK}}).<ref name=NH034112/><ref name=Nardana>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/812.html |title=Nardana |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=25 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Norman Queen||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: Convoy FN 426 or FS 429: The coaster was torpedoed and sunk in the [[North Sea]] off [[Happisburgh]], [[Norfolk]] by {{ship|German torpedo boat|S-102||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of 14 crew. One survivor was taken as a [[prisoner of war]].<ref name=NH034112/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Nurgis||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Norway}}\n|desc=World War II: The coaster was bombed and sunk in the [[English Channel]] {{convert|7|nmi|km}} west by north of [[The Lizard]], [[Cornwall]], United Kingdom by [[Heinkel He 111]] aircraft of [[Kampfgeschwader 2]], Luftwaffe. All 14 crew were rescued by {{SS|Arthur Wright||2}} ({{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}).<ref name=NH034112/><ref name=seekrieg194103/><ref name=Nurgis>{{cite web |url=http://www.warsailors.com/singleships/nurgis.html |title=D/S Nurgis |publisher=Warsailors |accessdate=1 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Prins Frederik Hendrik|1936|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Netherlands}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk in [[St George's Channel]] ({{coord|52|20|N|5|37|W}}) by [[Heinkel He 111]] aircraft of [[Kampfgeschwader 27]], Luftwaffe with the loss of eight crew.<ref name=NH034112/><ref name=seekrieg194103/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Tielbank||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Convoy SL 67]]: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean ({{coord|20|51|N|20|32|W}}) by {{GS|U-124|1940|2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of four of her 66 crew. Survivors were rescued by {{HMS|Forester|H74|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=NH034112/><ref name=Tielbank>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/811.html |title=Tielbank |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=25 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Togstun||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: Convoy FN 426 or FS 429: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the North Sea off [[Cromer]], Norfolk by {{ship|German torpedo boat|S-102||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of eight crew.<ref name=NH034112/> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==9 March==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=9 March 1941 |sort=}}\n